{
  "description": "The image depicts a rocky shoreline at low tide, with painted rocks in the foreground and a calm, expansive body of water extending to a distant, hazy landmass. Several large, grey rocks are clustered near the viewer, some bearing colorful, childlike graffiti or painted designs, including a prominent face on one. The tide is out, revealing a wide, flat expanse of wet sand and mudflats. Distant birds are visible as small white specks. The sky is overcast and grey, lending a subdued atmosphere to the scene. Dead vegetation, appearing as brown and yellow grass, is interspersed among the rocks. The land in the distance appears to be a low-lying coastline or urban area with buildings and infrastructure faintly visible through the haze.",
